.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Metadata \- NIP\-24 Extra Metadata Fields and Tags
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Metadata;
\&
\&    # Create a profile metadata event (kind 0)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->to_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        name         => \*(Aqalice\*(Aq,
\&        display_name => \*(AqAlice in Wonderland\*(Aq,
\&        about        => \*(AqNostr enthusiast\*(Aq,
\&        picture      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/avatar.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        website      => \*(Aqhttps://alice.example.com\*(Aq,
\&        banner       => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/banner.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        bot          => JSON::false,
\&        birthday     => { year => 1990, month => 6, day => 15 },
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse metadata from an event
\&    my $meta = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->from_event($event);
\&    say $meta\->name;          # alice
\&    say $meta\->display_name;  # Alice in Wonderland
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::Metadata\->validate($event);
\&
\&    # Standard tag helpers
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->hashtag_tag(\*(AqNoStr\*(Aq);  # [\*(Aqt\*(Aq, \*(Aqnostr\*(Aq]
\&    my $url = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->url_tag(\*(Aqhttps://example.com\*(Aq);
\&    my $title = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->title_tag(\*(AqMy Event\*(Aq);
\&    my $ext = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->external_id_tag(\*(Aqgithub:torvalds\*(Aq);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-24 (Extra Metadata Fields and Tags). Provides a builder and
parser for kind 0 metadata events with the extra fields defined by this NIP,
plus standard tag helper methods.
.PP
Kind 0 is a replaceable event. The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR is a stringified JSON object
containing the user\*(Aqs profile metadata. NIP\-01 defines \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`about\*(C'\fR,
and \f(CW\*(C`picture\*(C'\fR. This NIP adds:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`display_name\*(C'\fR \- an alternative, bigger name with richer characters
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`website\*(C'\fR \- a web URL related to the event author
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`banner\*(C'\fR \- a URL to a wide (~1024x768) background image
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`bot\*(C'\fR \- a boolean indicating automated content
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`birthday\*(C'\fR \- an object with optional \f(CW\*(C`year\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`month\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`day\*(C'\fR fields
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR should always be set regardless of \f(CW\*(C`display_name\*(C'\fR.
.SS "Deprecated fields"
.IX Subsection "Deprecated fields"
When parsing, the deprecated \f(CW\*(C`displayName\*(C'\fR field is mapped to
\&\f(CW\*(C`display_name\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`username\*(C'\fR is mapped to \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR. The canonical
field takes precedence if both are present. These deprecated fields
are never emitted by "to_event".
.SS "Standard tags"
.IX Subsection "Standard tags"
NIP\-24 defines standard tag meanings across event kinds:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR \- hashtag (value MUST be lowercase)
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`r\*(C'\fR \- a web URL the event refers to
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR \- name of sets, calendar/live events, or listings
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR \- external ID (see NIP\-73)
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 4
\&    my $meta = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->new(
\&        name         => \*(Aqalice\*(Aq,
\&        display_name => \*(AqAlice\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Metadata\*(C'\fR object. All fields are optional.
Croaks on unknown arguments. Typically returned by "from_event".
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS to_event
.IX Subsection "to_event"
.Vb 12
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->to_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,          # required
\&        name         => \*(Aqalice\*(Aq,              # recommended
\&        display_name => \*(AqAlice\*(Aq,              # optional
\&        about        => \*(AqHello\*(Aq,              # optional
\&        picture      => \*(Aqhttps://...\*(Aq,        # optional
\&        website      => \*(Aqhttps://...\*(Aq,        # optional
\&        banner       => \*(Aqhttps://...\*(Aq,        # optional
\&        bot          => JSON::true,           # optional
\&        birthday     => { year => 1990 },     # optional
\&        created_at   => time(),               # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 0 metadata Net::Nostr::Event. The metadata fields are
serialized as a JSON object in the event content. Only provided fields
are included in the JSON. Any remaining arguments are passed through to
"new" in Net::Nostr::Event.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $meta = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 0 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Metadata\*(C'\fR object. Returns
\&\f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event kind is not 0. Handles deprecated field names
(\f(CW\*(C`displayName\*(C'\fR \-> \f(CW\*(C`display_name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`username\*(C'\fR \-> \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR). Unknown
fields in the JSON are silently ignored (other NIPs define additional
fields like \f(CW\*(C`nip05\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`lud16\*(C'\fR, etc.).
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Metadata\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a kind 0 metadata event. Croaks if the kind is not 0 or the
content is not valid JSON. Returns 1 on success.
.SS hashtag_tag
.IX Subsection "hashtag_tag"
.Vb 1
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->hashtag_tag(\*(AqNoStr\*(Aq);  # [\*(Aqt\*(Aq, \*(Aqnostr\*(Aq]
.Ve
.PP
Returns a \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tag arrayref. The value is lowercased per the spec
requirement that hashtag values MUST be lowercase.
.SS url_tag
.IX Subsection "url_tag"
.Vb 1
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->url_tag(\*(Aqhttps://example.com\*(Aq);
.Ve
.PP
Returns an \f(CW\*(C`r\*(C'\fR tag arrayref for a web URL the event refers to.
.SS title_tag
.IX Subsection "title_tag"
.Vb 1
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->title_tag(\*(AqMy Event\*(Aq);
.Ve
.PP
Returns a \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR tag arrayref.
.SS external_id_tag
.IX Subsection "external_id_tag"
.Vb 1
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::Metadata\->external_id_tag(\*(Aqgithub:torvalds\*(Aq);
.Ve
.PP
Returns an \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tag arrayref for an external ID the event refers to.
See NIP\-73 for external ID formats.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS name
.IX Subsection "name"
The user\*(Aqs name (NIP\-01). Should always be set.
.SS display_name
.IX Subsection "display_name"
An alternative, bigger name with richer characters than \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR.
.SS about
.IX Subsection "about"
A description of the user.
.SS picture
.IX Subsection "picture"
A URL to the user\*(Aqs avatar image.
.SS website
.IX Subsection "website"
A web URL related to the user.
.SS banner
.IX Subsection "banner"
A URL to a wide (~1024x768) background image for the profile.
.SS bot
.IX Subsection "bot"
A boolean (\f(CW\*(C`JSON::true\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`JSON::false\*(C'\fR) indicating the content is
entirely or partially automated.
.SS birthday
.IX Subsection "birthday"
A hashref with optional \f(CW\*(C`year\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`month\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`day\*(C'\fR keys representing
the user\*(Aqs birth date. Each field MAY be omitted.
